review_blob: I usually think De Molen are wizards, but this one is to me dominated by soyasauce in the aroma as well as in the taste. The heavy malt profile and the alcohol level makes the beverage really thick and hard to drink.
This is a nice one! But in this years version i smell and taste something that reminds me of cold corncobs. Would like it a little sweeter.
Dark Amber with a nice warm-white head. Aroma of burned honey, caramel and some fruity hops. Nice mouthfeel.. Overall a nice beer
To me this is not a black IPA. It is a nice beer, but the raisins i find in the taste reminds me of a Barley or maybe  an Imperial. The mouthfeel is great.

This is to me a Barley wine. The alcohol is on top of things. I usually LOVE Stone Beer, but this one is a bit unbalanced. You should share this one with a couple of friends and, i guess, with some strong cheese instead of meat.
On tap at 19 Glas.Beautiful amber colour. Fresh fruity aroma. Pine and some citrus. Razerblade sharp bitterness.Extremely well balanced regarding 19 different hops.
